Pb$_{3}$O$_{4}$ has been observed in several structures (Wriedt, 1988; Dinnebier, 2003): \begin{itemize} \item Below 170K (Wriedt, 1988) it is in the \href{current_web_home_dir/A4B3_oP28_55_ghi_egh-001}{orthorhombic Minium-R structure}.  (Gavarri, 1978) tracks this structure up to 240K. \item Above 170K it is in the \href{current_web_home_dir/A4B3_tP28_135_gh_dh-002}{tetragonal Minium-T structure} (this structure). \item At ambient temperature the Minium-T structure transforms into what is apparently the Minium-R structure at a pressure between 0.11 and 0.3 GPa. (Dinnebier, 2003) call this {\em Phase II}. \item If the pressure is increased, between 5.54 and 6.6 GPa the structure transforms into orthorhombic \href{current_web_home_dir/A4B3_oP14_55_gh_ah-001}{Phase III structure}. \end{itemize} ~ \vspace{-.25in} 
 The first determination of this structure was made by (Gross, 1943), who assigned it to space group $P\overline{4}b2$ \#117 (ICSD 29094, AFLOW label A4B3\_tP28\_135\_gh\_dh-001), but that structure is practically indistinguishable from the current structure. 
 We assign tenary compounds related to this structure to prototype \href{current_web_home_dir/A4B2C_tP28_135_gh_h_d-001}{ZnSb$_{2}$O$_{4}$}.
